news.title: Ghaziabad development body may slap Gangsters Act for carrying out illegal constructions
news.para: GDA vice-chairperson RK Singh, who is also the DM, has instructed officials to prepare a list of illegal constructions in the city. He, officials said, will also hold talks with the police commissioner on how the drive can be carried out.

news.title: SC asks Authum Investments to implement resolution plan for Reliance Home Finance
news.para: The court, however, said that dissenting debenture holders should be given the option to accept the terms of the resolution plan or they can pursue other legal remedies to recover their dues.

news.title: No OCs to four-floor buildings without plan nod: DTCP
news.para: According to DTCP officials, many residential plot owners have constructed four-storey buildings whereas they got approval for only two floors.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh CM meets aggrieved Noida homebuyers, assures 'complete solution'
news.para: Yogi Adityanath met with a group of homebuyers' association NEFOWA from Greater Noida (West) also known as Noida Extension in Lucknow along with Singh.

news.title: US rent growth easing, but remains a burden for many tenants
news.para: The U.S. median rent rose 2.4% in January from a year earlier to $1,942, the lowest annual increase since June 2021, according to data from Rent, which tracks listings for apartment and rental houses.

news.title: Average long-term US mortgage rate hits three-month high
news.para: Mortgage buyer Freddie Mac reported Thursday that the average on the benchmark 30-year rate rose to 6.65% from 6.5% last week. The average rate a year ago was 3.76%.

news.title: Disconnect power to brick kilns in elephant corridor or face contempt: Madras HC tells Tangedco
news.para: A special bench of Justice N Sathish Kumar and Justice D Bharatha Chakravarthy issued the ultimatum on Thursday while hearing a batch of pleas seeking to seal the illegal brick kilns. The bench has directed the corporation to file a compliance report in February 6.

news.title: Kansai Nerolac Paints acquires 40% shares of Nerofix from Polygel for Rs 37 crore
news.para: 80,00,000 equity shares of Rs 10 each i.e. 40% of the total shareholding of Nerofix is being acquired. Post acquisition Kansai Nerolac Paints will hold 2,00,00,000 equity shares of Rs 10 each. The acquisition is expected to be completed by March 31, 2023.

news.title: Goa's town & country planning law to allow 'fixing of errors' in regional plan
news.para: The new legislation, which has received the governor’s approval, allows the chief town planner to correct “inadvertent errors” in a notified regional plan.

news.title: Ravi PNC Menon resigns as whole-time director of Sobha
news.para: Ravi PNC Menon will continue as a non-executive non-independent director of Sobha effective April 1, 2023. Subject to the approval of the board, he will also continue to hold the position of chairman (non-executive) of the company.

news.title: Nagpur: ED conducts searches at properties of Sandesh City's owner
news.para: An ED team of around 50 personnel landed at Agrawal's residence in Ramdaspeth in the morning and simultaneously searches were also started at the offices of Sandesh City Group and Sandesh Infrastructure.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh: 123 brick kilns in Bijnor issued closure notice
news.para: Additional DM Arvind Kumar served the notices to defaulters on Thursday. Among the defaulters, 22 are from Bijnor tehsil, 38 each in Dhampur and Chandpur, 16 in Najibabad and nine in Nagina area.

news.title: Won't vote if colony not handed over to Gurugram civic body: Mayfield Garden residents
news.para: The department of town and country planning (DTCP) on May 9 last year had ordered transfer of nine private colonies, including Mayfield Garden, to the MCG.

news.title: Embassy Group to sell certain portion of its shareholding in Embassy REIT to Bain Capital
news.para: With the paydown of this debt, it provides for a stronger balance sheet at Embassy Group with the goal to reduce overall debt by approximately 30 per cent before June 30, 2023, it said.

news.title: Why Gurugram is drowning in construction debris
news.para: MCG had earlier outsourced C&D waste collection and transportation to a private agency. The contract between the private firm and MCG, however, was put on hold after it was found to be allegedly involved in a Rs 50 crore scam.
